node.title: Heavy rain warnings extended for parts of North Island
node.description: MetService has extended heavy rain warnings and watches for parts of the North Island to later this evening.

node.title: U.S.-born figure skater representing China attacked online after falling during Olympics debut
node.description: The 19-year-old, who was born in California, changed her name and gave up her American citizenship to compete for China.

node.title: A Democrat takes over the F.D.I.C. after a partisan clash.
node.description: Martin J. Gruenberg replaced Jelena McWilliams, a Trump appointee who stepped down after a conflict with Mr. Gruenberg and two other Democratic members on the board.

node.title: Northland police arrest eight; methamphetamine, cash seized
node.description: Police have arrested eight people in Kaitaia and seized a quantity of methamphetamine and cash.

node.title: Winter Olympics: Snowboarder Zoi Sadowski-Synnott wins New Zealand's first ever gold
node.description: New Zealand has claimed its first ever gold medal at the Winter Olympics today, with Zoi Sadowski-Synnott winning the finals of the women's snowboard slopestyle event.

node.title: Police killing of Amir Locke spurs more protests in Minneapolis
node.description: A disturbing police bodycam video shows a SWAT team executing the early-morning warrant after using a key to enter the apartment.

node.title: Mystery of missing WWII soldier from Mississippi solved after 8 decades
node.description: The fate of Private Andrew Ladner had been unknown since he disappeared during World War II, during the Battle of Buna-Gona.

node.title: Five Minimalist Workout-Wear Brands to Know
node.description: To help ease you into the new year, and perhaps a new exercise routine, a roundup of lines offering clothes both functional and fashion-forward.

node.title: Fire Erupts at Brooklyn Building Under Construction
node.description: No injuries were reported, a New York Fire Department spokesman said on Monday. It was unclear whether residents in nearby buildings were required to evacuate.

node.title: Lawmakers press IRS to drop controversial selfie tool ID.me
node.description: Legislators say the tax agency's plan to require photos for people to access their accounts could invite cyberattacks.

node.title: First lady acknowledges free community college is dead, for now
node.description: Jill Biden said Congress has failed to pass the Build Back Better plan "and free community college is no longer a part of that package."

node.title: Queen Elizabeth II renews vow to carry on after 70 years on the throne
node.description: Life has thrown some curveballs at Britain's longest serving monarch, but she's not bowing out, and her trademark smile is as bright as ever.

node.title: Bicyclist falls to her death from rising drawbridge in Florida
node.description: Why the bridge tender began raising the span before it was cleared of pedestrians will be a focus of the investigation, police said.

node.title: Frontier and Spirit merging to form fifth-largest U.S. airline
node.description: Discount carriers say joining forces will let them offer more low-cost fares in the U.S., Latin America and Caribbean.

node.title: As Russia and U.S. add firepower, can a diplomacy blitz spare Ukraine?
node.description: Russian forces are set to hold war games in Belarus, with forces now just 30 miles from Ukrainian soil. But as the tension ramps up, so is the quest for a deal with Putin.

node.title: Kylie Jenner welcomes new baby
node.description: There's a new member of the Kardashian-Jenner clan.

node.title: NASCAR rumbles into Southern California
node.description: Busch Light Clash features numerous firsts in made-for-TV event in unlikely venue: the iconic LA Memorial Coliseum.

node.title: What's behind the push for a fourth stimulus check
node.description: IRS has distributed almost 170 million payments. But hardship remains widespread as the Omicron variant spreads.

node.title: Man located in Arizona after not knowing he won jackpot in Vegas
node.description: The gaming board identified Robert Taylor after two weeks of checking surveillance video, interviewing witnesses and reviewing ride-sharing data.

node.title: Teams USA wins silver in team figure skating as Russia takes gold
node.description: The U.S. earned the silver, thanks largely to a winning dance program from Madison Chock and Evan Bates.

node.title: Team USA's Vincent Zhou tests positive for COVID-19
node.description: The positive result may impact the 21-year-old's ability to compete in his next program, which is scheduled for tonight.

node.title: Days before 50th birthday, surfing icon Kelly Slater wins in Hawaii
node.description: Slater defeated a rider less than half his age to capture the Billabong Pro Pipeline near the renowned reef off of Oahu.

node.title: Spotify CEO: We're sticking with Joe Rogan despite controversy
node.description: Daniel Ek says he doesn't believe "silencing" Rogan is the answer to the massive pushback over Rogan's anti-coronavirus vaccine comments and racial slurs.

node.title: Search begins for legendary Antarctic shipwreck: "Lethal environment"
node.description: The story of Ernest Shackleton and his men is regarded "as the greatest survival story" of the 20th century, one historian said.

node.title: Mikaela Shiffrin falls and is disqualified from the giant slalom.
node.description: Shiffrin was a favorite going into the event, but her fall seconds into her first run opened the door for other competitors.

node.title: Navy SEAL candidate who died after Hell Week identified
node.description: The Navy said Seaman Kyle Mullen, of New Jersey, 24, and another aspiring SEAL were hospitalized in San Diego just hours after completing the grueling Hell Week.

node.title: Ireen Wüst becomes the first person to win individual golds at five Olympics.
node.description: The Dutch speedskater, 35, set an Olympic record in the 1,500 meters.

node.title: AOC crossing fingers skier Katie Parker will test negative to COVID on arrival in Beijing
node.description: The Australian Olympic Committee says there is a "reasonable probability" the alpine skier will test positive when she flies into Beijing on Tuesday.

node.title: Alvin Kamara arrested after Pro Bowl for alleged beating in nightclub
node.description: Authorities say the New Orleans Saints star running back was arrested hours after the game and charged with battery after an incident the night before.

node.title: Mikaela Shiffrin out early in giant slalom at Beijing Olympics
node.description: But star U.S. Olympian, who has several more events upcoming, vows to push on in bid to become first U.S. Alpine ski racer to win three Olympic golds across a career.
